MyBroadband’s 2019 Mobile Networks Conference will take place at The Venue in Melrose Arch on 11 April 2019, and has attracted an excellent speaker line-up. This exclusive technical conference will focus on mobile networks and mobile technologies, including 5G, fixed-LTE services, cellular antenna technologies, and IoT. The emcee for the event is Radio 702’s Aki Anastasiou, who will be joined by top speakers in the mobile networking field. ZTE and SqwidNet have partnered with MyBroadband and will be sponsoring the refreshments for the conference. To register for tickets or learn more about the 2019 Mobile Networks Conference, visit the conference website below. Please note that only 47 tickets are still available at the discounted rate, and these seats will be allocated on a first-come-first-served basis.